Subject: [PATCH 01/17] =?UTF-8?q?rk3576:=20RK3576=20NPU=20(rocket)=20bring?=
 =?UTF-8?q?-up=20=E2=80=94=20first=20working=20inference?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add support for the RK3576 NPU (RKNN) via the rocket DRM accelerator
driver and Mesa Teflon TFLite delegate.  Tested on Radxa ROCK 4D with
MobileNetV1 1.0/224 quantised:

  First-compile: ~50 ms   Steady-state: ~51 ms avg

Driver changes
--------------
rocket_drv.c: add "rk3576-rknn-core" to compatible match table
rocket_device.c: add for_each_compatible_node loop for rk3576-rknn-core
rocket_core.c/.h: add named clock IDs (aclk/hclk/npu/pclk); required
  because the RK3576 DT binding uses clock-names and devm_clk_bulk_get()
  needs the IDs set before the lookup
rocket_job.c:
  - rocket_job_timedout(): guard MMIO reads behind pm_runtime_active()
    to avoid faults when the job timer fires after runtime suspend
  - Add hrtimer-based completion polling for RK3576: OP_EN never clears
    on this SoC (unlike RK3588), so poll INTERRUPT_RAW_STATUS bits 28-29
    (PC_DONE_0/PC_DONE_1) instead; bits are read-only in INTERRUPT_MASK
    so they cannot be routed to the GIC

DT / binding changes
--------------------
rk3576.dtsi: add rknn_core_0/1, rknn_mmu_0/1 nodes with confirmed
  register addresses, IRQs (GIC_SPI 247/248), clocks, and resets
rk3576-rock-4d.dts: enable rknn_core_0/rknn_mmu_0; add npu-supply and
  regulator-always-on on vdd_npu_s0
rockchip,rk3588-rknn-core.yaml: make sram-supply optional (absent on
  RK3576)

Signed-off-by: Jiaxing Hu <huhuvmb88@gmail.com>
